  "texts": [
    "Inauthentic users like bots can be discounted, but profiling solely for counting purposes is not permitted.",
    "Providers should avoid double counting users across interfaces.For platforms, recipients on all sides engaging via exposure to or uploading content qualify, including consumers, traders, and advertisers.",
    "For search engines, only users submitting queries and seeing results are counted.",
    "The published numbers, reflecting methodology and average over 6 months, provide the basis for designating VLOPs and search engines.While publication is sufficient, providers are encouraged to also notify the numbers and methodology to the Commission and national coordinators to aid oversight.",
    "Other data sources may also be used for designations, subject to a right to be heard."
  ],
